(65, 60, 'Christina''s Journey', 'This is the story of Christina Anderson''s quest to live the perfect life.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; "><span style="line-height: 12pt; ">This is the first edition of The Never Ending Story. &nbsp;It''s up to you, our registered teen users, to tell Christina''s story. &nbsp;I will start the story then leave it up to all of our users, to write the next parts of the story. &nbsp;We don''t want any one person to tell the whole story, but instead, just tell the next piece of the story. &nbsp;Whether your piece of the story is one paragraph, one page, or one chapter, is up to you. &nbsp;Please submit your part of the story in the form of a comment, and we will piece the story together, and will continually update the story throughout the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">This story is called: Christina''s Journey</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><img src="/userfiles/image/Christina_Story1.jpg" width="387" height="250" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; ">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">This is the story of Christina Anderson and her quest to live the perfect life.</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Christina is a junior at Highland High School. &nbsp;She lives at home with her father, mother, two brothers and a sister. Her father just got laid off from the local lumber mill and her mother works as a receptionist at the paper mill. &nbsp;Money is very tight at the Anderson household, so Christina has just taken a job at the local Pizza Hut as a delivery driver. &nbsp;Even though her evening work schedule will cut into her study time, she needs money to pay for the insurance and gasoline in her 94 Mazda 626. &nbsp;Her car now has over 150,000 miles on the odometer, but along with her dad''s help, she has been able to keep her car in pretty good running condition.</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Christina is a an A and B student in school.and her love is the work she gets to do in the drama department. &nbsp;She loves to sign and act. &nbsp;Her dream is to someday leave this small logging town, and find her fame and fortune in Hollywood, or on Broadway. &nbsp;She feels like the bright lights are calling her name, but she also understands reality. &nbsp;The reality is, very few people ever get the opportunity to make it to the big time. &nbsp;For every person that succeeds in becoming a super star, there are tens of thousands of super star wannabees that never get the opportunity to live the perfect life she has dreamed of living.</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Now that her dad is out of work and money is tight for the whole family, her dreams of becoing a super star are looking less promising every day. &nbsp;She knows that with working the evening hours delivering pizza''s that she will have to give up working with the drama department, as she just won''t have the extra time necessary to prepare for performances. &nbsp;Things are definitely not going her way. &nbsp;That is, until one night she makes a delivery to the old mansion just outside of town.</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Now it''s your turn. &nbsp;Click on the comment button below, write the next part of the story, and then we will take your comments and add them to the story in the order that they were received.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; ">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>Annie1</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Sun Apr 08, 2012 15:57 pm</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">When she knocked on the door of the old mansion, it took a long time for someone to come to the door. When she finally heard someone unlock and open the door, she was presented with the view of an elderly lady who had to be in her 80''s. When the elderly lady saw that it was Christina delivering her pizza, she said, &quot;Come in my dear and I will get your money for you&quot;. When Christina entered the house, she felt like she was entering a movie theater, as the old decorations and posters that adorned the walls, seemed like something she had seen in movie theaters a long time ago.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>Vt1</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Tue Apr 10, 2012 04:38 am</small></td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n                        <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Noticing the interest that Christina was displaying in her decorations, the old woman said, &quot;Do you like old theater memorabilia?&quot; Christina said, &quot;I love the theater. It has long been a dream of mine to be able to act professionally. Your house is so amazing. Where did you get all of these things?&quot; The old woman said, &quot;I used to be an actress. In my day, I starred in many movies as well as participated in theater productions on Broadway.&quot; Christina was just awestruck that someone famous lived in her town. &quot;What is your name&quot; Christina asked.</span></span></p>\r\n                        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>Annie1</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Wed Apr 11, 2012 04:51 am</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">&quot;My name is Monica. Monica Tinsdale&quot; replied the elderly lady. I know that name, thought Christina. All of the sudden it was as if a light had turned on. Monica Tinsdale was a very famous actress that Christina''s mom and dad had talked about when she was a little girl. But what was a famous actress like Monica Tinsdale doing living in their town. A million questions started racing through Christina''s mind. Things she would love to ask, but didn''t dare intrude on Monica''s privacy.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; "> Seeing the confused look on Christina''s face, Monica asked, &quot;Is something wrong my dear?&quot; For the longest time, Christina couldn''t answer. Finally, she was able to ask, &quot;What are you doing living here in our town?&quot; Monica just smiled and said, &quot;Why don''t you come over here and sit down. I''d love to talk with you for a few minutes.&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>Vt1</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Thu Apr 12, 2012 04:21 am</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-size: larger; "><span style="font-family: Arial; ">Christina sat down and just stared in awe of this very famous actress. Monica began, &quot;The reason that I came to live in this town has to do with my grandparents. When I was little, my grandparents built this house and I used to come here on my summer vacations. I''ve always had fond memories of this home and the wonderful times I was able to spend here,&quot; she said. &quot;My grandparents passed away almost 70 years ago, and after their deaths, this house was sold. Over the years, this house has gone through a number of owners, and about 10 years ago, I got the opportunity to buy it, and this is where I decided I want to live out the rest of my life.&quot; Monica then said, &quot;Tell me about yourself child.&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>JR</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Fri Apr 13, 2012 04:43 am</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Christina then proceeded to tell Monica about herself. When she finished telling Monica, Monica asked, &quot;How are Ted and Cynthia doing?&quot; &quot;You know my parents&quot; Christina asked? &quot;My dear, I make it my business to know everyone in our town&quot; Monica replied. &quot;In fact, you''d be surprised that I know you. I have watched you with great interest for many years now. The reason I have taken notice of you is because you remind me so much of me when I was your age. It is very seldom that I see someone with your poise, maturity, and how at ease you are with your stage performances&quot; Monica replied. &quot;You''ve seen me perform,&quot; Christina asked. &quot;Child, I first saw you perform at the Christmas pageant when you were in Miss Welkers sixth grade class&quot; she said. &quot;After I saw your performance there, I made a point of going to all of your plays and school programs after that. That is why I was thrilled to see you come to my door this evening&quot; explained Monica.</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>JR</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Sun Apr 15, 2012 06:52 am</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Christina just sat there. Stunned that someone as famous as Monica would know her name, let alone having watched her over the years and taken such an interest in her. When she finally composed herself enough to speak, Christina asked, &quot;Why would you take an interest in me? I''m really not anyone special.&quot; Monica said, &quot;My dear, I want to spend a little bit of time with you. Would you be ok with that?&quot; Christina told her that she because she was working, they should probably do this another time. Monica wasn''t going to take no for an answer so she called Christina''s boss at the Pizza Hut. She explained that she wanted to have Monica spend some time with her this evening, and that she would make it up to him later. &quot;Yes Ms Tinsdale&quot; he said. He knew well that what Monica Tinsdale wants, Monica Tinsdale always gets.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; "> &quot;Now that''s settled&quot; Monica said. She continued, &quot;There''s a few things about me that you need to know.&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>Andrew</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Tue Apr 17, 2012 04:38 am</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">&quot;When I was a little girl, my father owned a cartage company, and therefore, he was gone a lot. I was an only child, so my mother and I spent a lot of time at home together. One of the favorite things for my mother and myself, which we did every Saturday, was to go into town and watch a movie. As there weren''t a lot of new movies that came out in those years, we would usually watch the same movie over, and over again. I got to the point where I could sing all of the songs, and dance all of the dances, that were shown in each movie. My mother used to say ''Monica, you are so good at singing and dancing. Someday we will be watching you singing and dancing at the movies.'' My Mother was so special that way. She always encouraged me to follow my heart, and she supported me in everything I wanted to do.&quot; Monica looked at Christina and said, &quot;Having watched your mother as she always attended your school plays and choir concerts, she has reminded me a lot of my own mother.&quot; &quot;You are very lucky to have had someone as special as your mom, encouraging you all along the way.&quot; Christina told Monica that she was very thankful to have such a special mom. </span></span></p>\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">Christina then told Monica that she was having to give up performing with the drama department because of her dad being unemployed and her work schedule taking up most of her evenings. &quot;I''m sorry to hear that&quot; Monica replied. &quot;What do your parents think of your decision&quot; she asked? &quot;It was a hard decision to have to make, but mom and dad realize that with these tough economic times, sacrifices have to be made&quot; said Christina. &quot;I need to help my family make it through these struggles&quot; she said. &quot;I understand&quot; said Monica, &quot;but what if there were a way for you to still keep doing your theatrical work and also bring in some extra money? Would you be interested?&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; ">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="89%" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><strong>Annie1</strong>&nbsp;Says:</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; "><small>Sat Apr 21, 2012 15:13 pm</small></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" valign="top" class="runningtext" style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n            <p><span style="font-family: Arial; "><span style="font-size: larger; ">&quot;Would I be interested?&quot; Christina almost shouted. &quot;Of course I would be interested. That would be like a dream come true!&quot; &quot;Well then, I have a proposition for you&quot; replied Monica. &quot;Ever since my housekeeper moved away last month, it has been extremely difficult to keep up with all of my housework, and I just haven''t found anyone that I really like that could take her place. If you would be willing to come to my home three days a week to help me with my cleaning and things around the house, I would be willing to work with you and teach you all that I know about acting and pay you for your time as well.&quot; Christina didn''t have to even think twice before she said, &quot;That would be great!&quot; &quot;Good&quot; said Monica. &quot;And I will call your boss at Pizza Hut and let him know that you are going to come to work for me. Come back here Wednesday after school, and we will get started.&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="line-height: 12pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'blog_13338127494f805e0dd3564.jpg', '2012-04-06 21:33:46', 'Inactive', 'home', 0),
